From 75df88a293cd4d9bae928c5d4db21ff43351ad26 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 12:15:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Lockscreen: pin status bar to top, match systemui icon
 size

The keyguard window (z=4) was inset by SystemUi_StatusBar's safe area
even with setWindowLayoutFullScreen + expandSafeArea, leaving a ~72px
gap above the lockscreen status bar icons. The lockscreen status bar
also rendered smaller than systemui's because the bundled SVG assets
in screenlock have different internal padding than systemui's.

- StatusBar wrapper gets .offset({y: -36}) to pull it into the safe-area
  region the system reserves for the system status bar (36vp on the X23).
- status_bar_height bumped 24vp -> 36vp so the lockscreen bar matches
  the systemui bar height. status_bar_margin_top 4vp -> 0 (the offset
  alone positions it).
- accounts_area_margin_top 40vp -> 32vp to keep the rest of the lockscreen
  layout (clock, prompt, accounts) at the same y as before.
- signal/wifi SVG assets in screenlock/features/{signal,wifi}component
  replaced with the matching systemui assets (only signal_{3,4,no} differ
  byte-wise; the rest were already identical). The shared assets render
  with the same internal padding so the icon shapes match the unlocked
  status bar.
- common base float: signal_fontSize 16fp -> 12fp; battery_fontSize added
  at 12fp so the lockscreen text matches systemui's 12fp rendering.
- product/phone base float: also gets status_bar_height 36vp and the
  matching status_bar_margin_top/accounts_area_margin_top overrides.
- Drop the unused mHeightPx arg from the SlideScreenLock call in
  product/phone/.../pages/index.ets; SlideScreenlock never declared
  mHeightPx so newer ArkTS treated this as an error.

